{"id":4167,"date":"2024-02-29T07:50:36","date_gmt":"2019-12-30T02:20:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=4167"},"modified":"2024-11-25T00:28:07","modified_gmt":"2024-11-24T18:58:07","slug":"modular-wardrobe-designs","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/modular-wardrobe-designs\/","title":{"rendered":"Modular Wardrobe Designs To Transform Your Bedroom (Blah To Beautiful)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p> M<em>odular wardrobes can take a simple room and transform it to a space that suddenly looks spacious. How do they do that? Let\u2019s find out!<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wardrobes can be visible or invisible. It depends on how they are made. They are among the most inconspicuous pieces of furniture in a home, yet which packs the most punch. They are discrete, often unseen and are built for the sole purpose of storage. In the last few decades however, wardrobes have undergone a magical transformation. They\u2019ve become stylish, trendy, enticing and so much more. As much as their purpose has remained the same, what has changed is their look and feel. <strong>Modular wardrobes<\/strong> have been a godsend to modern, contemporary homes. Homes that don\u2019t like to confine themselves to a dated period, homes that flaunt their spaces and the things in it.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Modular wardrobes as the name suggests are easy fit storage spaces, can be made and dismantled easily, are sleek and run unobtrusively against walls. Unlike heavy wooden, almirahs that rarely deviated from a standard design, today\u2019s wardrobes are outfitted with glass, chrome and metal, in colours as varied as white to red and styles that go from L-shaped to parallel designs. Some of these contemporary modular wardrobes also have enhanced functionalities &#8211; retrofitted with a folding bed or table as a space saving measure or floor to ceiling to maximise storage space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/modular-kitchen-design\/\">designs in modular kitchens<\/a> are varied, versatile and it can get difficult making your choice. Does functionality matter to you or the look? Will storage suffice for the next five years or would you want to change the design? You must ask yourself questions like these before you undertake any kind of work on your wardrobe.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Modular wardrobe designs are plentiful, as already discussed. To make things easy, we have listed three major design concepts derived from simple ones to where colour and bedroom spaces define them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Smart Modular Wardrobe Designs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As the name suggests, smart wardrobes are designed intelligently keeping in mind the larger picture and purpose. Think of intelligence that far exceeds ordinary furniture. There are many different variations of smart wardrobes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Wardrobes With Hidden Beds<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Space-saving wardrobes aren\u2019t storage furniture of choice but when factored in intelligently, can make quite a difference. If your bed is occupying space and you live in a small apartment where bedrooms can double up as an entertainment zone or for relaxation, this is a great option to explore. Folding beds are generally built into the wardrobe so they come with foldable legs and can be folded away when not in use. They are built with sturdier material and the wardrobe is designed in such a way that it has lots of storage too. This same design applies to an integrated TV unit that can be tucked away when not in use. In children\u2019s bedroom spaces, foldable beds can double up as study tables. This affords functionality as well as is a great design.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000115\/modular-wardrobe-with-hidden-beds-foldable-bed.jpg\" alt=\"Modular wardrobe with a sleek foldable bed discreetly hidden away in the wardrobe for small bedroom\" class=\"wp-image-4168\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000115\/modular-wardrobe-with-hidden-beds-foldable-bed.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000115\/modular-wardrobe-with-hidden-beds-foldable-bed-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000115\/modular-wardrobe-with-hidden-beds-foldable-bed-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000115\/modular-wardrobe-with-hidden-beds-foldable-bed-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Simple small bedroom made spacious with a sleek foldable bed discreetly hidden away in the wardrobe<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Wardrobes That Divide Your Walls, Not You<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Wardrobes can also be designed in such a way as to divide bedrooms into different functional spaces. If you have a huge bedroom and want to create boundaries, make a walk-in wardrobe with a sliding door. Position the wardrobe in such a way that functional spaces are clearly demarcated according to their use.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000118\/modular-wardrobe-design-with-glass-partition-walls.jpg\" alt=\"Modular wardrobes divide your walls with glass partition that divide a large room into different functional sections\" class=\"wp-image-4169\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000118\/modular-wardrobe-design-with-glass-partition-walls.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000118\/modular-wardrobe-design-with-glass-partition-walls-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000118\/modular-wardrobe-design-with-glass-partition-walls-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000118\/modular-wardrobe-design-with-glass-partition-walls-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Discreet glass partition walls that divide a large room into different functional sections<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Complete home interiors with modular wardrobe solutions\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/15143320\/complete-home-interiors-with-modular-wardrobe-solutions.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Wardrobes That Hide Away All Your Stash<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Wardrobes and beds often don\u2019t merge. There is a clear space demarcation for these two types of furniture. However, when space above beds are fitted with wardrobe storage cabinets instead of being left untouched, it can maximise space quite considerably.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000122\/modular-wardrobe-storage-cabinets.jpg\" alt=\"Modular wardrobe storage cabinets, it can maximise space for small bedrooms\" class=\"wp-image-4170\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000122\/modular-wardrobe-storage-cabinets.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000122\/modular-wardrobe-storage-cabinets-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000122\/modular-wardrobe-storage-cabinets-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000122\/modular-wardrobe-storage-cabinets-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Shelves above the bed act as little storage spaces for knick knacks clothes and other essentials<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Latest Wardrobe Designs for Bedroom | 10 Best Wardrobe Design Ideas | Sliding Wardrobe Design\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/qXAglK-T_D8?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Trendy Modular Wardrobe Designs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Stylish, trendy wardrobes are not just functional but look good too. They embellish bedrooms, make them brighter and add a sense of design to the space. Here are a few key ideas that take a wardrobe from dreary to stylish.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Outer Facade That Keeps You Hooked<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Wardrobes are simple if not for their outer facade. Gone are the days of boring wood and paneling. Instead, modular wardrobes designs now have glass or mirror finishes, layering and blending of materials, texturing and more. Looking for pretty decor to entice you to your bedroom? You don\u2019t need anything when your wardrobe makes up for it.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000125\/modular-wardrobes-designs-glass-mirror-finishes.jpg\" alt=\"Modular wardrobes designs with glass or mirror finishes, layering and blending of materials makes beautiful bedroom\" class=\"wp-image-4171\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000125\/modular-wardrobes-designs-glass-mirror-finishes.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000125\/modular-wardrobes-designs-glass-mirror-finishes-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000125\/modular-wardrobes-designs-glass-mirror-finishes-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000125\/modular-wardrobes-designs-glass-mirror-finishes-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Glossy surface of a two-toned wardrobe that does away your need for a mirror<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Embrace a clutter free life with functional wardrobe designs\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/16114642\/clutter-free-life-with-functional-wardrobe-designs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Corner Spaces To Hide More Than Just Those Shoes<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>What is waste in the bedroom when that can be put to good use? Even corner spaces if need be! Contemporary wardrobes make use of all available spaces. Empty corners in recesses make for great storage spaces for jewellery and undergarments, even shoes and winter wear. Wardrobes when designed to not just look good but store a lot as well, reflect intelligent design. Moreover L-shaped shelves work well and this design must be made use of to the maximum.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000129\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobe-design.jpg\" alt=\"L-shaped modular wardrobe make for great storage spaces for jewellery and undergarments, even shoes and winter wear\" class=\"wp-image-4172\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000129\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobe-design.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000129\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobe-design-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000129\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobe-design-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000129\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobe-design-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">An L-shaped wardrobe that has space to store everything one needs from head to toe<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also read about <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/corner-wardrobe-designs\/\">Corner Wardrobes: Stylish Solutions for Small Rooms<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Designer Cabinets That Spice Up Wardrobes<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cabinets are a given in contemporary wardrobes. What sets them apart is how smartly they are designed. Vintage wardrobes can be paired with contemporary cabinets, Wooden wardrobes can be stylised as classics. Cabinets can be longer from end-to-end, or smaller peppered all over. Think of making the most with little; let storage and design lead the way.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000132\/modular-wardrobe-cabinets-for-storage.jpg\" alt=\"Modular wardrobe cabinets gives bedroom extra storage, its smart design idea for modular wardrobe design\" class=\"wp-image-4173\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000132\/modular-wardrobe-cabinets-for-storage.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000132\/modular-wardrobe-cabinets-for-storage-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000132\/modular-wardrobe-cabinets-for-storage-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000132\/modular-wardrobe-cabinets-for-storage-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">See how these cabinets built into the wardrobe give this bedroom extra storage? Now that is smart design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Modular Wardrobe Types<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Wardrobes aren\u2019t as boring as we make them to be. They are shaped differently and can carry off different silhouettes. This entirely depends to what extent your imagination stretches. Consider wardrobes malleable and work them around your bed or the window and decide their shape accordingly. How do we go about this? Let&#8217;s discuss below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Straight Wardrobes That Mean Business<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Designed all along one wall, straight wardrobes form a simple design sense from the outside. They are placed in such a way so as to be unobtrusive, unhindered, complementing the bedroom while blending in all the time. Straight designs can be modular and compartmentalised, freestanding and dismantable or contemporary with open shelves. Their choice mainly depends on your bedrooms\u2019 immediate needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000137\/tall-straight-modular-wardrobes.jpg\" alt=\"Straight modular wardrobes to be complementing the bedroom while blending in all the time\" class=\"wp-image-4174\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000137\/tall-straight-modular-wardrobes.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000137\/tall-straight-modular-wardrobes-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000137\/tall-straight-modular-wardrobes-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000137\/tall-straight-modular-wardrobes-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">all straight modular wardrobes complement and blend with traditional bedrooms<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">L-Shaped Wardrobes Hugging Two Walls<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Contrary to straight ones these go off the beaten path. Built along two walls, L- shaped wardrobes can limit the possibilities of use of different materials. Also they need to be planned well, especially closure so they don\u2019t clash with other furniture. They do afford plenty of space and storage, can be experimented with and most importantly optimise corner storage which otherwise often gets wasted.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000140\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobes-for-storage.jpg\" alt=\"L shaped modular wardrobes afford plenty of space and storage\" class=\"wp-image-4175\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000140\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobes-for-storage.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000140\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobes-for-storage-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000140\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobes-for-storage-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000140\/l-shaped-modular-wardrobes-for-storage-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">L-shaped wardrobes occupy more space but pack in so much more<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Give your wardrobe a designer look!\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/16140549\/wardrobe-designer-look.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Walk-in Wardrobes Emphasising Royalty<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Walk-in closets as the name suggests can just be walked at anytime. They resemble these elaborate cubbies that hold all the treasures in the world. In essence walk-in wardrobes can be designed with even a little space. If there is a corner that is too small to place a furniture yet large enough for shelves, then convert it into a walk-in wardrobe. Build floor to ceiling shelves, some attractive lighting place for clothes, shoes, mirrors and the works. There\u2019s more than can be done here than in standalone wardrobes in bedrooms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000144\/walk-in-modular-wardrobe-design.jpg\" alt=\"Walk-in modular wardrobes build floor to ceiling shelves, some attractive lighting place for clothes\" class=\"wp-image-4176\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000144\/walk-in-modular-wardrobe-design.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000144\/walk-in-modular-wardrobe-design-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000144\/walk-in-modular-wardrobe-design-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/12\/21000144\/walk-in-modular-wardrobe-design-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Walk-in wardrobes that look spacious and feel exclusive and make dressing fun<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One among majorly two kinds of bedroom furniture, wardrobes have come along way from being just fly-on-the-wall furniture to mean a lot more. They are an integral part of bedroom design and can make or break the look of the bedroom. How you do this is by selecting a design you love, that complements your bedroom and one you\u2019ll look forward storing your clothes in.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Also Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/glass-wardrobe-design\/\">Glass Wardrobe Designs For Your Bedroom<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/womens-wardrobe-design-ideas\/\">Women\u2019s Wardrobe Design<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/kids-bedroom-interiors\/kids-wardrobe-designs\/\">Kids Wardrobe Design Ideas<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Unwind In Your Personal Sanctuary<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with modular interiors<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.c